&lt;p>Discover devices via CoIoT&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="synopsis">Synopsis&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Discover Shelly devices on the network using CoIoT multicast.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>CoIoT is a protocol used by Gen1 Shelly devices to announce their presence
on the local network. This command listens for CoAP announcements on the
multicast group 224.0.1.187:5683.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Gen1-specific information displayed:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Device type and firmware&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Number of relays and meters&lt;/li>
&lt;li>CoIoT status values&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>



